<HR><H2>time in the log</H2>
<H3>daemon@ATHENA.MIT.EDU (Fri May 20 09:53:54 1994
)</H3>
<PRE>
Date: Thu, 19 May 1994 14:00:34 -0700
From: rayn@q.crossaccess.com (Ray Nawara jr.)
To: coldstuff@MIT.EDU

I definitely dont think time should be made in-db. That makes it
modifiable from the db, and therefore prettymuch invalid as a logging
tool security-wise. I do agree that a compile option on format would
be nice, but i think a log should get as much detail as possible, and
just have other tools (like grep and sed) extract what you want from
this. The ability to have a log of the verbose format, or of Lyncx's
brief format, or any other reasonable format makes sense to me.

	Ray / Ash


</PRE>
